# 🎬 VistaPlay – Movie Recommendation App

## 📖 Overview

**VistaPlay** is an online movie streaming and recommendation app that helps users discover trending, popular, and personalized movie suggestions.  
It features a modern user interface with search, filtering, and detailed movie pages, powered by a **Firebase backend** and deployed on **Vercel**.

Built with **Next.js (React)** and styled using **Tailwind CSS**, VistaPlay ensures a responsive and optimized user experience.

---

## ✨ Features

- 🔎 **Movie Search & Browse:** Find movies by title, genre, or keyword.
- 📈 **Trending & Popular Movies:** Dynamic display of trending content.
- 🎥 **Detailed Movie Pages:** Overview, cast, ratings, and related movies.
- ⭐ **Recommendations:** Suggestions based on user preferences/history.
- 🔐 **Authentication:** User sign-up/login with Firebase Auth.
- 📂 **Watchlist & Favorites:** Save and manage personal movie lists.
- 🌙 **Dark Mode Support:** Theme toggle for user-friendly UI.
- 🚀 **Fast Deployment:** Hosted on Vercel with GitHub integration.

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** Next.js (React), Tailwind CSS
- **Backend/Database:** Firebase (Firestore, Authentication, Storage)
- **Deployment:** Vercel
- **API Handling:** Firebase SDK / REST API
- **Version Control:** Git + GitHub

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```bash
VistaPlay/
├── public/                 # Static assets (images, icons, etc.)
├── src/
│   ├── components/         # Reusable UI components (Navbar, Footer, MovieCard, etc.)
│   ├── pages/              # Next.js pages (index.tsx, movies/[id].tsx, etc.)
│   ├── constants/          # Static constants (genres, routes, configs)
│   ├── interfaces/         # TypeScript interfaces (Movie, User, etc.)
│   ├── assets/             # Custom images, logos
│   ├── utils/              # Helper functions
│   ├── lib/                # Firebase config & API setup
│   └── styles/             # Global styles (if any beyond Tailwind)
├── .env.local              # Environment variables (Firebase keys, API keys)
├── package.json
├── README.md
└── tsconfig.json
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup & Installation

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/vistaplay.git
   cd vistaplay
   ```

2. **Install dependencies**
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

3. **Set up environment variables**  
   Create a `.env.local` file in the root directory and add your Firebase config:
   ```
   NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key
   NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_auth_domain
   NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
   NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_storage_bucket
   NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_sender_id
   NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id
   ```

4. **Run locally**
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```
   Visit [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000).

5. **Build for production**
   ```bash
   npm run build
   npm start
   ```

---

## 🔥 Firebase Integration

- **Firestore:** Stores movies, watchlists, and user preferences.
- **Firebase Auth:** Handles login/signup (Email/Password, Google, etc.).
- **Firebase Hosting/Storage (optional):** Store images or static movie posters.

> **Note:** Enable Firestore Database and Authentication in the Firebase Console.

---

## 🚀 Deployment (Vercel)

1. Push your project to GitHub.
2. Go to [Vercel](https://vercel.com/).
3. Click **New Project** → Import your GitHub repo → Select VistaPlay.
4. Add environment variables in Vercel Project Settings.
5. Deploy. Vercel will auto-build and provide a live link.

---

## 🎮 Usage

- Visit the deployed app.
- Sign up or log in to personalize your experience.
- Browse trending and recommended movies.
- Add movies to your Watchlist.
- Click any movie for details (cast, reviews, related suggestions).

